title: For Sale/Trade:  HK P2000 9mm V2 LEM w/ Night Sights and Extra's!
postcontent: I have an HK P2000 9mm with a V2 LEM up for sale. This actually has the "Light LEM" springs in it right now.This is listed as a DA/SA pistol but this is the LEM. Technically LEM is still a type of DA/SA but not the tradition DA/SA as most would think. You have a VERY light pull to the back, you hit that wall and then the break. It's more like a striker but, not... I assume if you're reading this you probably know what HK LEM is.The gun itself has Meprolight night sights, and the HK 45 extended magazine. I also have 5 magazines, two of which have flat base plates for easy carry and comes with a holster. I've also got the case, the back straps etc.Some  would argue the P2000 LEM is the perfect carry gun if your an HK fan. I've seen coutless people say the LEM is the way to go if you want a better than a striker like trigger but still prefer a hammer. I love HK pistols but I definately prefer the DA/SA guns over the LEM. All of my other HK's are DA/SA and I've always just felt more comfortable carrying DA/SA over LEM or striker fired.I would like to trade this for another HK 9mm with that is DA/SA. Ideally I'd like to even trade pistol for pistol the P2000 9mm V2 LEM for an HK P2000 9mm V3. I would also concider trading full package for full package for maybe an HK P30 or P30L in 9mm. The only striker fired gun I would concider is a GLOCK 19 Gen4 MOS, I'd like to attach a RMR to one and have it be a range only gun. Shoot me a PM if your interested in knowing more.

Takedown version with earlier take-down lever introduced approx 1901 (replaced with a take-down screw in 1924). 22.5" octagonal barrel chambered in .32 rimfire. This model, manufactured from 1890 to 1933, was Remington's smallest rolling block rifle. Enterior barrel dings, otherwise very good collector condition, good bore, functions perfectly, test-fired. Also included is 1 scarce vintage box (50 - 2 for test fire = 48) of Remington Kleanbore .32 Long Rim Fire cartridges. FTF, ID, North Chesterfield area.

title: For Trade:  Winchester Model 21 16 Gauge SxS
postcontent: The Model 21 is an American icon and its reputation is well deserved.  A strikingly handsome gun with the finest steels, gunners in the know have utilized the Winchester Model 21 in the field and at the club to shoot thousands of rounds without failure.  IF YOU LIKE HEAVY LOADS FOR PHEASANTS OR OTHER TOUGH GAME, THIS IS THE GUN.  Most double gun enthusiasts are well aware of the reputation earned by the Winchester Model 21; a gun of mechanical genius that was under the micro management of John Olin himself.  With only 30,000 produced (compared to 250,000 Parkers!), any high condition Model 21 is a valuable, investment quality firearm.  For the 16ga. fan you will notice that there were few M21’s made in 16ga. and most are 7lb. guns or better.  To find a 6 ½ lb. 16 gauge capable of shooting the stoutest magnum loads, with 28” LM/F chokes, you have found the perfect pheasant and western field gun, and the perfect late season grouse gun.  For the man who really knows the double gun world, having 2 triggers is a must so that you might pick your chokes as you mount the gun.  There are very few double trigger, splinter forend M21 guns to be found.  This gun, sn5873 made around 1934, is an early M21 Field Grade in factory original condition with mirror bores, 97% factory blue, 93% factory receiver blue, barrels tight as new on the hinge pin and the breech face, perfect screws and mechanics, nicely refinished factory original stock with excellent checkering, great shooting dimensions, and balanced perfectly between your hands.  When you pick this gun up you can’t believe it is a M21…no bulkiness.  This is a “VFI CERTIFIED” gun (a $275 service in our shop), having been completely disassembled, ultrasonic cleaned, inspected, properly lubricated and reassembled, ready for decades more use, and now carries a 90 day mechanical warranty.  We have priced this fine M21 so it is affordable and being an 80 year old Model 21, it will increase in value as you enjoy its use.  Thanks for looking!
